description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Would you like to be part of innovative new developments? CPFT has been in the forefront of changes in the way mental health care is delivered across Primary and Secondary Care Adult Community Mental Health. This is an exciting opportunity to be part of shaping the way forward and influencing how things develop now and in the future.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Primary Care Mental Health Service (PCMHS) is an award-winning service which is receiving national interest as a new and innovative way of working, recently winning the Positive Practice Award in the Primary and Community Adult MH Services category at the National Positive Practice Awards in Mental Health. We were also ‘highly commended’ in the Innovation in Community MH award category. This was made possible by the highly skilled, committed and motivated staff in every discipline throughout the PCMHS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The PCMHS also support the transition of service users form secondary care services into primary care and our Recovery Coach Team which is integrated within the service work alongside people who are struggling with this transition.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an energetic and enthusiastic &lt;strong&gt;Band 5 Recovery Coach&lt;/strong&gt; to join the Recovery Coach Team element of the service in the &lt;strong&gt;Cambridge&lt;/strong&gt; locality. The ideal candidate will have a strong team work ethic, excellent coaching and communication skills, the ability to build and maintain relationships across primary care, secondary care and 3rd sector organisations, and experience of working with clients with mental health issues in groups or in one to one to meet their mental health and social needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will work alongside the Adult Locality Teams and the wider PCMHS. They will be well supported by senior clinical and managerial staff, offering regular supervision and reflective practice sessions with colleagues. We hold a well-attended service governance meeting, where all staff have the opportunity to creatively contribute to service quality and development. We also value the experience and knowledge candidates can bring to the service and positively encourage initiative and creative thinking.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cambridgeshire and Peterborough NHS Foundation Trust (CPFT) provides integrated community and mental health, learning disability and social care services of the highest standard due to our continued commitment to quality and service improvement. We aim to support people of all ages to achieve the very best they can for their health and wellbeing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CPFT have strong links with Cambridge University and is actively engaged in a variety of important research areas in mental health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are looking for a new challenge, enjoy variety in your work and wish to be part of a team striving to make a difference for our community by supporting people with mental health needs then we want to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For part time posts - salary will be pro-rata.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please do make contact with us if you would like to discuss any of the above in further detail, or talk about the role, we would be pleased to hear from you. We would also welcome an informal visit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Francis Atiemo - 07980911016&lt;/p&gt;
